1
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:07,160
(A WeTV Original)

2
00:00:09,570 --> 00:00:11,380
♪Way Way to You♪

3
00:00:16,530 --> 00:00:18,480
♪Way Way to You♪

4
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:30,820
♪On My Way to You♪

5
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:35,060
=Way To You=

6
00:00:35,060 --> 00:00:35,970
(Highlights)
Anytime,

7
00:00:35,970 --> 00:00:36,930
anywhere,

8
00:00:36,930 --> 00:00:38,530
super detectives

9
00:00:38,530 --> 00:00:40,110
taking every case seriously!

10
00:00:40,110 --> 00:00:42,330
I think what I gained most
was friendship.

11
00:00:42,910 --> 00:00:44,310
I gained a lot of validation too.

12
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:47,790
For me, this was such a great journey.

13
00:00:48,950 --> 00:00:52,940
Hi, everyone. Welcome to Way To You!

14
00:00:57,470 --> 00:00:59,660
Next up, we're announcing

15
00:00:59,950 --> 00:01:01,490
Best Duo.

16
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:04,640
First place

17
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:05,630
and second place.

18
00:01:06,910 --> 00:01:08,280
First place is...

19
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:12,780
The champions
with the highest team score are...

20
00:01:12,780 --> 00:01:15,330
(Who will take the crown?)

21
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:18,360
Next, let's do
a chemistry quiz challenge.

22
00:01:18,360 --> 00:01:20,430
(Chemistry Quiz Rules)
The three of you will get a prompt

23
00:01:20,430 --> 00:01:23,010
and write your answers
on the board at the same time.

24
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:24,970
If your answers match, you win.

25
00:01:24,970 --> 00:01:25,960
Whoa.

26
00:01:26,150 --> 00:01:27,240
This is fun.

27
00:01:28,210 --> 00:01:29,780
(Question 1: Who is the hardest
to cheer up?)

28
00:01:30,410 --> 00:01:32,030
(I can answer this one.)

29
00:01:34,620 --> 00:01:35,930
I'm ready.

30
00:01:35,930 --> 00:01:38,070
Okay. Three, two, one.

31
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:47,750
(Same move)

32
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:48,460
U.Jay.

33
00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:49,320
(Same answer)

34
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,580
Everyone picked me.

35
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:51,990
(Why is U.Jay the hardest to cheer up?)
Maybe because he's

36
00:01:51,990 --> 00:01:53,690
the first Leo friend I've ever had.

37
00:01:53,690 --> 00:01:54,640
I just...

38
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,420
(Can't explain it)

39
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:57,740
I don't get it yet.
I still don't really understand.

40
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,010
He just works himself up.

41
00:02:00,010 --> 00:02:01,300
(He works himself up)
What can you even do?

42
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:08,280
I feel like U.Jay really
has that fire sign personality.

43
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,570
(Definitely a fire sign)
He can be pretty explosive.

44
00:02:09,570 --> 00:02:10,860
Sometimes we'd be in the makeup room.

45
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:12,000
One time, we were changing clothes.

46
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,960
U.Jay was talking to me,

47
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:15,880
but I honestly couldn't hear him.

48
00:02:15,880 --> 00:02:16,660
There were too many people.

49
00:02:16,660 --> 00:02:17,830
Noise here, noise there.

50
00:02:17,830 --> 00:02:18,900
Everybody talking.

51
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,320
I seriously had no idea in that moment.

52
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:22,390
Then when we got back
to the hotel, he started

53
00:02:22,390 --> 00:02:23,640
(Blowing up)
blowing up.

54
00:02:27,660 --> 00:02:31,000
First of all, I'm an INFP.
I'm like a little butterfly.

55
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,180
And I'm a Leo too.

56
00:02:32,180 --> 00:02:33,960
So I'm really sensitive.

57
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,050
(Notices every detail)
I pick up

58
00:02:36,050 --> 00:02:37,600
on the tiniest things.

59
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:40,930
That one detail can affect
my whole mood for the day.

60
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:42,120
Like what Eugen just said.

61
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:44,020
About him ignoring me, right?

62
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:44,810
Because for me,

63
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:46,930
if someone's talking to me,

64
00:02:46,930 --> 00:02:47,990
I can tell who it is.

65
00:02:48,060 --> 00:02:50,270
So when I call him and say something,

66
00:02:50,270 --> 00:02:52,120
and he doesn't respond,

67
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:52,920
I start thinking,

68
00:02:53,850 --> 00:02:55,630
why are you mad at me again?

69
00:02:55,630 --> 00:02:57,570
Then my temper just flares up.

70
00:02:57,810 --> 00:02:58,890
But then again,

71
00:02:58,890 --> 00:03:00,200
I'm also really easy to cheer up.

72
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:01,660
As long as he comes over
and says something,

73
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:02,780
I'm fine again.

74
00:03:02,780 --> 00:03:05,030
(Quick to flare up, quick to calm down)
I calm down right away.

75
00:03:05,690 --> 00:03:08,200
But I've grown a lot compared to before.

76
00:03:08,200 --> 00:03:11,570
Because sometimes something
really crosses a line,

77
00:03:11,570 --> 00:03:15,000
and that's when I really blow up.

78
00:03:18,140 --> 00:03:19,980
(Question 2: Who takes
the most selfies?)

79
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:21,020
Selfies?

80
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:22,270
(Answers right away)

81
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:28,230
I wrote Eugene.

82
00:03:28,230 --> 00:03:29,110
I wrote Eugene too.

83
00:03:29,110 --> 00:03:30,300
Why me?

84
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,690
(Suspicious.)
I think it's U.Jay.

85
00:03:31,690 --> 00:03:34,090
Yeah. That's just what I've seen too.

86
00:03:34,090 --> 00:03:34,990
(We all saw it)
Yeah. He grabs his phone

87
00:03:34,990 --> 00:03:35,870
and starts snapping.

88
00:03:35,870 --> 00:03:37,640
Yeah, I put Eugene.

89
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,580
(Sharp eyes)
Because I've seen it happen

90
00:03:39,580 --> 00:03:40,580
so many times.

91
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:43,100
That just proves you pay
a lot of attention to me.

92
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:44,670
How could I not? You do it
right in front of me.

93
00:03:44,670 --> 00:03:45,400
How would I miss it?

94
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,670
(Time to tease Eugene)
Like this? I still can't see it?

95
00:03:46,670 --> 00:03:48,800
I just feel like anytime he's alone
and not next to me

96
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,950
he's off taking selfies.

97
00:03:49,950 --> 00:03:51,610
(If he suddenly goes quiet,
he's definitely taking selfies.)

98
00:03:51,610 --> 00:03:52,030
Same.

99
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:54,640
(Joining in)
I always see him taking selfies.

100
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:57,460
Like, we could just be sitting there
resting or whatever,

101
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:59,750
and he'll suddenly whip out his phone
and start snapping.

102
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:01,230
So I don't get why he picked me.

103
00:04:01,230 --> 00:04:01,930
Why, though?

104
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:02,970
Why me?

105
00:04:03,380 --> 00:04:04,820
Maybe I just pay more attention to you.

106
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:06,960
Every time he takes selfies,
he never asks me to join.

107
00:04:09,470 --> 00:04:10,680
(Always ready to snap)
This is good.

108
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,210
One, two, three.

109
00:04:14,660 --> 00:04:15,510
Okay, Pippin.

110
00:04:17,850 --> 00:04:18,350
Your head.

111
00:04:21,209 --> 00:04:21,920
I'll do it.

112
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,340
Pippin,

113
00:04:23,570 --> 00:04:24,610
don't rub against the pen.

114
00:04:26,180 --> 00:04:27,550
There's like no light on my face.

115
00:04:27,550 --> 00:04:28,830
(Time quietly passes)
Turn a little this way.

116
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,050
Okay.

117
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,980
(Takes three shots in a row)

118
00:04:34,980 --> 00:04:37,180
(Question 3: Who acts the cutest?)

119
00:04:37,890 --> 00:04:39,360
This one's kinda hard.

120
00:04:41,070 --> 00:04:41,550
Okay.

121
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:44,700
(Another instant answer)

122
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,400
One, two, three.

123
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,560
Why'd you vote for me, Pippin?

124
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,530
Because you're so good at acting cute.

125
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:54,840
When I first met him,
I said one thing to him.

126
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:55,490
I said,

127
00:04:55,490 --> 00:04:57,250
"Eugene, even though you're older..."

128
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:58,320
(Watch what you say.)
Even though you're older?

129
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,670
I'm not that old.

130
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:03,520
Even though you're older...

131
00:05:03,930 --> 00:05:05,920
(Let me explain first)
To me, on this show,

132
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,620
(Zip it)
you're

133
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:08,630
the cutest person here.

134
00:05:08,630 --> 00:05:11,130
So I fully allow you
to keep acting cute all you want.

135
00:05:12,620 --> 00:05:13,100
Okay.

136
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:13,680
(Wants to learn)
Teach us.

137
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,620
(Eager)
Yeah, show us.

138
00:05:15,860 --> 00:05:18,550
Stay with me. Come on.

139
00:05:21,010 --> 00:05:22,100
That's not how you sound.

140
00:05:22,100 --> 00:05:23,580
Then how do I sound? Show me.

141
00:05:24,740 --> 00:05:25,240
Like this.

142
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,940
Pippin!

143
00:05:27,940 --> 00:05:30,000
(Same move)
Pippin, come with me

144
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,010
to the convenience store!

145
00:05:31,010 --> 00:05:34,500
Pippin!

146
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,340
Come to the convenience store with me!

147
00:05:36,340 --> 00:05:37,560
I'm not like that!

148
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,310
You totally are!

149
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:39,470
That's exactly you!

150
00:05:39,470 --> 00:05:41,470
A perfect reenactment.

151
00:05:41,570 --> 00:05:44,120
(There's always someone watching)

152
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:47,400
Out of the three of you,
who talks the most?

153
00:05:47,670 --> 00:05:48,860
(That one's easy)

154
00:05:52,780 --> 00:05:54,420
(Correct)

155
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:57,030
Out of the three of you,
who gives off little brother vibes?

156
00:05:57,030 --> 00:05:58,600
Little brother vibes?

157
00:06:05,330 --> 00:06:07,250
(Correct)

158
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:09,270
Is there a rabbit too?

159
00:06:09,270 --> 00:06:10,170
Judy.

160
00:06:11,050 --> 00:06:11,960
An autograph.

161
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:13,360
Alright, next question.

162
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:15,360
Out of the three of you,
who's the best dancer?

163
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:21,990
Three, two, one.

164
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:23,650
Cannon.

165
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:26,140
(Officially recognized as the dance guy)

166
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:28,600
I'm not that good.

167
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:32,320
I just feel like maybe
I've got some basics.

168
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:35,490
(Has more dance experience)
I've had more dance training than them.

169
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,470
Thanks.

170
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:41,960
When the show ends,
who's gonna cry the hardest?

171
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:46,100
After the show ends?

172
00:06:49,860 --> 00:06:51,460
(Cannon's answer: No one)

173
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,730
I haven't seen

174
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:58,060
anyone cry after the show.

175
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,370
He still doesn't know.

176
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:03,490
But if you ask who looked
the saddest on the show,

177
00:07:03,490 --> 00:07:04,630
I think it was probably Poom.

178
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:07,140
(The sad prince)

179
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:10,180
It's the last episode now,
so I guess we'll find out soon.

180
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:11,810
A surprise?

181
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:13,660
Go watch it.

182
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:19,310
Out of the three of you,
who's the most caring?

183
00:07:28,130 --> 00:07:30,950
Honestly, everyone
takes care of each other.

184
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:34,170
It feels like everyone
worries about one another.

185
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:38,800
Last question. You've all
been partnered with Eugene,

186
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,380
right?

187
00:07:39,380 --> 00:07:39,940
Yeah.

188
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:43,320
So if he got to choose again right now,

189
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,030
which one of you three would he pick?

190
00:07:55,190 --> 00:07:55,760
Really?

191
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:59,000
When he was with Cannon,
he looked really at ease.

192
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,010
Oh, I didn't get that vibe.

193
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:05,680
In the last episode, Poom
and Eugene were paired up, right?

194
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:09,160
It just felt like those two
were always hanging out.

195
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:13,460
So I figured they must
be pretty close by now.

196
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:16,570
I think Eugene is really cute,

197
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:18,150
so I like messing with him.

198
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:20,800
Every time I think of Team China,

199
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:23,020
his face just pops into my head.

200
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:24,360
Alright, time to mess with him again.

201
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,360
If you ask who teases Eugene the most,

202
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,260
that'd be me.

203
00:08:28,260 --> 00:08:30,960
I think he probably thinks of me too.

204
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:34,780
You look pretty proud.

205
00:08:34,780 --> 00:08:35,390
I think

206
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:37,470
he's gotten pretty close
to me lately too.

207
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:39,610
So if we go back to day one,

208
00:08:39,610 --> 00:08:42,179
and Eugene had to choose
between Cannon and Poom,

209
00:08:42,429 --> 00:08:44,290
Cannon, do you think you'd
try to steal him back?

210
00:08:44,290 --> 00:08:45,230
What would you do?

211
00:08:47,050 --> 00:08:48,890
Of course I'd steal him.

212
00:08:48,890 --> 00:08:51,180
Honestly, I would too, if we
were picking from day one.

213
00:08:52,060 --> 00:08:53,870
Then I pick

214
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:54,540
Poom.

215
00:08:57,560 --> 00:09:02,020
(Question 1: If nationality
didn't matter, who would Ryu choose?)

216
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,590
(Done writing)

217
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:08,980
I'm done.

218
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,800
That was fast.

219
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:14,940
(Different answers)

220
00:09:16,620 --> 00:09:17,940
(You picked me?)
Me?

221
00:09:17,940 --> 00:09:18,940
(Of course)

222
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:20,500
(Touched)

223
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:21,250
Deaw.

224
00:09:21,350 --> 00:09:22,210
Deaw.

225
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:22,760
Really.

226
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:23,610
Really?

227
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,140
He's lying!

228
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:25,430
Really.

229
00:09:25,430 --> 00:09:26,350
He just wrote something random.

230
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:27,660
(That's not what I meant)

231
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:28,480
I mean this.

232
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:31,200
In your heart, you picked Deaw.

233
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,520
But you wrote me down.

234
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,500
No.

235
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,240
It's not like that.

236
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,020
(Hear me out first)
No.

237
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:36,600
Yes.

238
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,270
No.

239
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:38,910
Honestly, there are a lot of reasons.

240
00:09:38,910 --> 00:09:40,590
But let me explain.

241
00:09:40,590 --> 00:09:41,400
I'm not very good with words.

242
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:44,980
But the time I've spent with him,

243
00:09:44,980 --> 00:09:47,090
living together, hanging out together,

244
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:50,950
I'm really happy with him. Yeah.

245
00:09:51,310 --> 00:09:52,060
Comfortable.

246
00:09:52,340 --> 00:09:53,400
Really comfortable.

247
00:09:54,580 --> 00:09:55,440
Okay.

248
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:58,320
Which of you two is funnier?

249
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,520
(I need to think about this first)

250
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,760
(Both cracking up)

251
00:10:02,940 --> 00:10:03,690
I'm done.

252
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:04,700
Okay.

253
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:08,280
Three, two, one.

254
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:11,130
Me.

255
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:17,850
Me.

256
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,040
Okay.

257
00:10:19,040 --> 00:10:20,050
(They got it right)

258
00:10:20,050 --> 00:10:20,780
Okay.

259
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:22,720
Alright, next question.

260
00:10:22,820 --> 00:10:25,330
Which one of you is more of a slowpoke?

261
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:29,920
You.

262
00:10:32,740 --> 00:10:34,340
Three, two, one.

263
00:10:36,290 --> 00:10:37,110
(They got it right)

264
00:10:37,110 --> 00:10:39,390
Why? Tell us what he's done.

265
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:41,520
(It's a long story)
Oh boy.

266
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:44,210
A few times, we were both free,

267
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:45,630
so I asked him to hang out.

268
00:10:45,630 --> 00:10:47,780
I said we could film some videos too.

269
00:10:47,780 --> 00:10:51,400
We planned to meet at 3 p.m.
By 5, I asked where he was.

270
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,210
He said, "Fifteen more minutes."

271
00:10:53,210 --> 00:10:54,600
Fifteen minutes later, I asked again.

272
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,680
He said, "Ten more minutes."

273
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:56,830
Ten minutes later, I asked again.

274
00:10:56,830 --> 00:10:57,920
He said, "Three more minutes."

