00:25:02,490 --> 00:25:06,440
Who do you like the most on the show?
Name one person.

564
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,980
(I need a favorite rival)

565
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:09,430
Your favorite.

566
00:25:10,630 --> 00:25:12,070
(Please be me)

567
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,910
(Picks Deaw)
I pick Deaw.

568
00:25:31,110 --> 00:25:31,750
What about you?

569
00:25:34,310 --> 00:25:36,420
(Gets along with Cannon)
What is this now?

570
00:25:37,290 --> 00:25:38,850
I just feel happy around him.

571
00:25:42,780 --> 00:25:44,400
(Still sees U.Jay like an idol)
I was like, wow, he's so handsome.

572
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:46,810
So I kept secretly looking at him.

573
00:25:46,810 --> 00:25:48,260
But I didn't want him to notice.

574
00:25:48,260 --> 00:25:49,320
I was like, wow, he's really handsome.

575
00:25:49,740 --> 00:25:52,430
(Picks Eugene)
I pick Eugene.

576
00:25:55,940 --> 00:25:58,010
Honestly, Eugene and I...

577
00:25:58,670 --> 00:26:00,250
actually talk more.

578
00:26:00,250 --> 00:26:01,830
Compared to U.Jay,

579
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:04,020
Eugene and I talk more.

580
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:05,660
So since I have the chance today,

581
00:26:05,660 --> 00:26:07,980
I want to ask U.Jay something.

582
00:26:10,070 --> 00:26:11,000
I want to ask U.Jay.

583
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:17,180
Are we good friends?

584
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:21,340
Because honestly, with U.Jay,

585
00:26:21,340 --> 00:26:23,470
I've always had this idol filter.

586
00:26:23,470 --> 00:26:24,790
(Idol filter)

587
00:26:24,790 --> 00:26:27,100
One night, I was in their room,

588
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:29,540
and U.Jay showed me a video

589
00:26:29,540 --> 00:26:30,880
of one of his stage performances.

590
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:33,660
For a second, I was totally stunned.

591
00:26:33,660 --> 00:26:35,860
I was like, wow,
someone like a real idol

592
00:26:35,860 --> 00:26:37,820
is actually sitting right next to me.

593
00:26:37,820 --> 00:26:40,020
And we watched it

594
00:26:40,020 --> 00:26:42,940
together there,

595
00:26:42,940 --> 00:26:44,470
and it felt unreal.

596
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:47,080
(Admiration)
It just felt like, wow,

597
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:49,690
he really is an idol.

598
00:26:50,730 --> 00:26:53,500
So today I really wanted
to ask U.Jay this.

599
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:57,040
Do we count as good friends?

600
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:00,890
I think that's
a hard question to answer.

601
00:27:00,890 --> 00:27:02,180
As for the good-friends part,

602
00:27:02,180 --> 00:27:03,380
honestly, from the heart,

603
00:27:03,380 --> 00:27:04,380
I don't think so.

604
00:27:06,530 --> 00:27:08,640
To be honest, I think there's
still some distance between us.

605
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:11,840
(Still some distance)
Because every time we talk,

606
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:14,060
I can feel that when you talk to me,

607
00:27:14,060 --> 00:27:16,060
you're still a little guarded.

608
00:27:16,060 --> 00:27:17,140
(Still guarded)
It doesn't feel that close.

609
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:17,460
Like,

610
00:27:17,460 --> 00:27:19,300
when you're chatting with Eugene,

611
00:27:19,300 --> 00:27:21,040
I can feel that good-friends vibe.

612
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,970
Like really opening up and all that.

613
00:27:22,970 --> 00:27:23,730
But with me,

614
00:27:23,730 --> 00:27:26,860
sometimes you don't really
say what's on your mind.

615
00:27:26,860 --> 00:27:28,770
(Can't fully open up)
Or maybe you're not that open with me.

616
00:27:28,770 --> 00:27:30,670
So if we're talking about good friends,

617
00:27:30,670 --> 00:27:33,420
I think we still need
a little more time.

618
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:34,930
But we're friends now.

619
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:35,850
Okay.

620
00:27:36,640 --> 00:27:37,990
Okay, I'm done asking.

621
00:27:38,490 --> 00:27:39,350
Pippin, any more?

622
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:40,580
Then let's ask one.

623
00:27:40,580 --> 00:27:41,790
(A reward question)
Eugene,

624
00:27:41,790 --> 00:27:45,960
out of everyone on this show,

625
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:47,220
(A very familiar question)

626
00:27:47,220 --> 00:27:51,510
who makes you feel the most relaxed
and comfortable?

627
00:27:51,510 --> 00:27:53,610
Sorry, you can only ask
the same question once.

628
00:27:53,610 --> 00:27:54,410
You need a different one.

629
00:27:54,410 --> 00:27:55,760
I changed it. I added
a bunch of qualifiers.

630
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:56,930
You didn't say any of that just now.

631
00:27:56,930 --> 00:27:59,510
Most comfortable,
most relaxed, happiest.

632
00:28:01,640 --> 00:28:03,820
(Nicely played)

633
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:04,650
Everyone.

634
00:28:04,650 --> 00:28:05,580
(Mr. Neutral)

635
00:28:05,580 --> 00:28:06,650
(Not accepted)
I don't accept that.

636
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:07,520
I can only pick one?

637
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:08,230
Only one.

638
00:28:08,230 --> 00:28:09,780
Just like how you made me pick one.

639
00:28:10,660 --> 00:28:12,800
Then I pick Poom.

640
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:13,700
(Picked Poom)

641
00:28:13,700 --> 00:28:15,490
(My turn)
Okay, here's mine.

642
00:28:15,490 --> 00:28:18,640
(A mischievous idea appears)
If Poom were visiting China,

643
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:21,590
and at the same time I asked you
to come see me in Chengdu,

644
00:28:21,590 --> 00:28:23,740
where would you go?

645
00:28:23,860 --> 00:28:26,060
(A hard question to answer)

646
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:28,800
Who are you asking? Pippin?

647
00:28:28,800 --> 00:28:29,770
(Switching targets)
You.

648
00:28:29,770 --> 00:28:31,440
You just said you'd pick Poom.

649
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:32,980
So now I'm asking you.

650
00:28:33,320 --> 00:28:35,020
(One thing leads to another)

651
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:37,160
(Think fast, brain)

652
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,720
That's a good question.

653
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:40,710
(Question of the century)
Let me think.

654
00:28:41,250 --> 00:28:43,600
Then I'm...

655
00:28:44,150 --> 00:28:45,960
ditching you.

656
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:46,510
Ditching me?

657
00:28:46,960 --> 00:28:47,860
(Yep)

658
00:28:47,860 --> 00:28:49,660
Go shoot without me.

659
00:28:49,660 --> 00:28:50,620
He turned and walked away.

660
00:28:51,170 --> 00:28:52,800
Like he'd made up his mind.

661
00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:54,330
He didn't even look at me again.

662
00:28:54,660 --> 00:28:55,570
Just kidding.

663
00:28:55,570 --> 00:28:56,280
(Best friends holding hands)
Just kidding.

664
00:28:56,280 --> 00:28:57,930
I'd go to Chengdu first.

665
00:28:57,930 --> 00:28:58,540
Really?

666
00:28:58,540 --> 00:28:59,170
Yeah.

667
00:28:59,580 --> 00:29:00,250
No.

668
00:29:00,250 --> 00:29:01,340
Really.

669
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:02,320
That didn't feel sincere.

670
00:29:02,610 --> 00:29:03,200
For that question,

671
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,180
(Helping a friend recover)
I already thought

672
00:29:04,180 --> 00:29:05,480
of a good answer for him.

673
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:06,540
A really good one.

674
00:29:08,070 --> 00:29:10,260
(Online relationship advice)
Didn't he say he had to reject someone?

675
00:29:10,260 --> 00:29:11,820
Then I'd make up a reason
and say to Poom,

676
00:29:11,820 --> 00:29:12,930
"Why would I go to Chengdu?"

677
00:29:12,930 --> 00:29:14,430
Or say Chengdu has more fun stuff to do.

678
00:29:14,430 --> 00:29:15,700
Then he wouldn't have to go
to Shanghai to see him.

679
00:29:15,700 --> 00:29:16,710
And Poom could fly to Chengdu too.

680
00:29:16,710 --> 00:29:18,270
That way all three of you
can meet in Chengdu.

681
00:29:18,270 --> 00:29:19,690
(Lesson learned)
Very nice.

682
00:29:20,340 --> 00:29:22,130
(Easy work)

683
00:29:22,130 --> 00:29:23,900
I asked Cannon,

684
00:29:24,330 --> 00:29:26,350
from the first day you met me

685
00:29:26,350 --> 00:29:27,270
until now,

686
00:29:27,990 --> 00:29:29,350
have you noticed any change in me?

687
00:29:29,350 --> 00:29:30,180
(Blurts out)
Yes, yes.

688
00:29:30,180 --> 00:29:30,860
Give me a moment.

689
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:33,540
Let me think...

690
00:29:35,310 --> 00:29:36,290
about how to put it.

691
00:29:36,290 --> 00:29:39,140
At the beginning,

692
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:41,800
you seemed distant and hard to approach.

693
00:29:43,230 --> 00:29:44,000
Why act like that?

694
00:29:44,980 --> 00:29:46,240
Go on, I'm listening.

695
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:49,570
At first, I thought Poom
was difficult to approach

696
00:29:49,570 --> 00:29:50,170
like someone

697
00:29:50,650 --> 00:29:54,420
with high emotional walls. But after

698
00:29:56,140 --> 00:29:58,090
getting to know you,
I realized that was only

699
00:29:58,320 --> 00:29:59,320
your first-day impression.

700
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:04,900
My initial impression

701
00:30:05,340 --> 00:30:06,980
was that you were friendly but quiet.

702
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:09,910
The kind of person one could
exchange a few words with,

703
00:30:11,100 --> 00:30:13,310
just not someone who talks much.

704
00:30:15,020 --> 00:30:16,790
On the first day I met you,

705
00:30:16,790 --> 00:30:17,880
I was the outgoing one.

706
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:18,860
But by the end of the show,

707
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:20,470
after everything,
I've become more reserved.

708
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:22,760
I don't believe that.

709
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:23,250
You don't?

710
00:30:23,250 --> 00:30:23,970
No.

711
00:30:24,140 --> 00:30:25,700
I don't, because after

712
00:30:26,050 --> 00:30:28,310
spending some time with you,

713
00:30:28,850 --> 00:30:30,120
I realized you're quite talkative

714
00:30:30,390 --> 00:30:32,450
and playful as well.

715
00:30:32,450 --> 00:30:33,980
Just not quite as much as I am.

716
00:30:35,940 --> 00:30:38,040
May I ask, did you ever find me intimidating?

717
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:39,050
(Yes.)
Intimidating.

718
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:41,210
On our first meeting,

719
00:30:41,860 --> 00:30:42,470
I thought...

720
00:30:43,420 --> 00:30:45,030
he knows how to carry
himself with authority.

721
00:30:45,870 --> 00:30:47,740
To be honest, the first time we met.

722
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:48,740
What's your name?

723
00:30:49,270 --> 00:30:50,650
You're playing on a tablet.

724
00:30:50,900 --> 00:30:51,570
Cannon.

725
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:54,790
So composed.

726
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,720
At that moment,

727
00:30:57,070 --> 00:30:58,580
I thought he'd
be the most formidable here,

728
00:30:58,850 --> 00:31:01,560
here to compete only.

729
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:04,040
(A professional contestant.)

730
00:31:05,570 --> 00:31:06,010
Alright.

731
00:31:06,010 --> 00:31:06,650
(Do you have question?)

732
00:31:06,650 --> 00:31:07,280
You have?

733
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:08,170
Yes, I do.

734
00:31:08,700 --> 00:31:10,300
(Let me hear it.)
Why do you have?

735
00:31:12,140 --> 00:31:14,980
If Deaw and I both

736
00:31:15,740 --> 00:31:16,800
fell into the water,

737
00:31:17,340 --> 00:31:19,590
(Deaw and I, whom would you save?)
whom would you save?

738
00:31:19,590 --> 00:31:21,460
(Pauses to think.)

739
00:31:21,460 --> 00:31:23,400
- Both of you.
- Give him a moment.

740
00:31:23,780 --> 00:31:24,500
Only choose one.

741
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,540
Both of you.

742
00:31:25,540 --> 00:31:26,300
Only one.

743
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:27,480
Two.

744
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:31,880
I would throw you a lifebuoy,
then go and rescue Deaw.

745
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,520
So the lifebuoy is for Deaw?

746
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:34,900
He gets the lifebuoy

747
00:31:34,900 --> 00:31:36,030
and then he comes to save me.

748
00:31:36,300 --> 00:31:37,500
How would you know?

749
00:31:37,930 --> 00:31:39,540
(I know you well enough.)
Alright, alright.

750
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,130
(Master of diplomacy.)

751
00:31:41,770 --> 00:31:44,170
(I have another question.)

752
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:46,520
If I

753
00:31:47,330 --> 00:31:48,470
cannot swim

754
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,380
and Deaw,

755
00:31:53,690 --> 00:31:54,700
(If we both fell into the water,
who would you save?)

756
00:31:54,700 --> 00:31:55,850
who would you choose?

757
00:31:58,600 --> 00:31:59,610
I would save neither of you.

758
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,520
I can't swim.

759
00:32:03,620 --> 00:32:04,690
I would call for help.

760
00:32:05,180 --> 00:32:07,640
(I would seek someone more
professional to rescue you.)

761
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:10,820
Help! Help!

762
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:12,640
That wouldn't be of any assistance.

763
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:13,640
I truly cannot swim.

764
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:14,900
If I were to jump in,

765
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:17,460
(Do you accept?)
there'd be three people needing rescue.

766
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:19,390
That's true.

767
00:32:19,960 --> 00:32:21,880
Three people would be in danger.

768
00:32:22,700 --> 00:32:27,220
If you were to visit China,

769
00:32:27,970 --> 00:32:29,280
would you go to Shanghai

770
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,020
or Beijing?

771
00:32:31,250 --> 00:32:32,310
(Shanghai or Beijing for a trip
to China? Answer me properly.)

772
00:32:34,470 --> 00:32:36,400
Shanghai has Kai.

773
00:32:37,990 --> 00:32:38,860
There's shopping

774
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:43,460
And Pippin is there. Everyone is there.

775
00:32:44,490 --> 00:32:45,140
Shanghai.

776
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:46,440
Beijing has none of that.

777
00:32:46,510 --> 00:32:47,210
Beijing.

778
00:32:47,540 --> 00:32:50,860
Beijing has you,

779
00:32:52,110 --> 00:32:52,810
doesn't it?

780
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:53,850
Yes.

781
00:32:53,850 --> 00:32:54,810
What else does it have?

782
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:56,190
It has...

783
00:32:56,910 --> 00:32:58,550
Only you.

784
00:32:58,550 --> 00:32:59,500
Only me.

785
00:33:00,540 --> 00:33:01,270
I will go to Shanghai.

786
00:33:01,570 --> 00:33:03,860
(Playfully)

787
00:33:04,520 --> 00:33:04,970
I'm joking.

788
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:07,580
(You had better be.)

789
00:33:09,300 --> 00:33:10,780
(Thinking)

790
00:33:11,170 --> 00:33:12,140
(Watching attentively)

791
00:33:14,130 --> 00:33:15,130
Let me go first.

792
00:33:16,870 --> 00:33:20,780
Both of you have partnered
with me and with U.Jay.

793
00:33:21,820 --> 00:33:22,500
Choose one.

794
00:33:26,140 --> 00:33:27,330
(For better or worse?)

795
00:33:29,340 --> 00:33:30,180
Choose one?

796
00:33:30,180 --> 00:33:30,820
Yes.

797
00:33:32,100 --> 00:33:34,250
(As a friend.)
Choose one to be your closest friend.

798
00:33:34,250 --> 00:33:36,630
(As a partner.)
Choose one to be your best partner.

799
00:33:36,940 --> 00:33:37,620
Mhm.

800
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:40,050
You're so bad.

801
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:44,760
(Be honest.)
Tell me the truth.

802
00:33:49,950 --> 00:33:52,780
For me, I would choose you.

803
00:33:52,780 --> 00:33:53,360
(Choosing Kai.)

804
00:33:53,360 --> 00:33:54,910
For both.

805
00:33:54,910 --> 00:33:55,720
For both? Truly?

806
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:57,240
(Both options are Kai.)
Wow, really?

807
00:33:57,240 --> 00:33:57,960
Yes.

808
00:33:59,500 --> 00:34:02,100
From the beginning, Kai and I

809
00:34:02,100 --> 00:34:05,270
shared the same room,

810
00:34:05,270 --> 00:34:09,910
so we had more opportunities
to communicate,

811
00:34:11,040 --> 00:34:12,280
especially about work.

812
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:13,720
We partnered for a week,

813
00:34:13,720 --> 00:34:17,290
during which we had
to rehearse a performance,

814
00:34:17,290 --> 00:34:19,340
both singing and dancing.

815
00:34:19,340 --> 00:34:21,960
I feel that during that week,

816
00:34:22,200 --> 00:34:24,590
we worked very well together.

817
00:34:24,590 --> 00:34:26,410
We developed a strong
understanding of each other.

818
00:34:26,550 --> 00:34:28,090
(They gradually built mutual chemistry.)

819
00:34:30,420 --> 00:34:31,430
Oh no.

820
00:34:32,090 --> 00:34:33,040
This is very hard.

821
00:34:37,250 --> 00:34:39,700
(They must face the same choice again.)

822
00:34:42,940 --> 00:34:44,820
(U.Jay and Kai choose Leo.)

823
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:47,190
(Leo chooses U.Jay.)

824
00:34:47,190 --> 00:34:52,040
I choose Kai as...

825
00:34:52,180 --> 00:34:54,420
(Who will he choose this time?)

826
00:34:56,660 --> 00:34:58,610
(This is too difficult.)

827
00:35:06,990 --> 00:35:10,960
In truth, I have two considerations.

828
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:13,610
With Kai,

829
00:35:13,610 --> 00:35:16,350
as a closest friend,
if we were to be partners,

830
00:35:16,530 --> 00:35:20,040
our work would progress very quickly.

831
00:35:20,580 --> 00:35:21,550
As for U.Jay,

832
00:35:21,550 --> 00:35:24,900
working with him

833
00:35:25,220 --> 00:35:27,210
feels very easy.

834
00:35:27,210 --> 00:35:29,860
Yes, the two of them are quite similar.

835
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:32,860
You're very good at balancing.

836
00:35:33,420 --> 00:35:34,940
This is really difficult for me.

837
00:35:35,260 --> 00:35:36,260
As for me,

838
00:35:37,030 --> 00:35:38,120
I have a question as well,

839
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:39,950
actually, it is the same question.

840
00:35:40,670 --> 00:35:43,260
(Turning the question back.)

841
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:45,590
You understand your own
question now, don't you?

842
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:47,100
When you worked with me,
what did you think?

843
00:35:47,100 --> 00:35:47,870
(He wants to know Kai's feelings.)

844
00:35:48,260 --> 00:35:49,330
How did you feel?

845
00:35:49,330 --> 00:35:51,410
When working with Deaw,

846
00:35:51,410 --> 00:35:53,180
everything felt very smooth.

847
00:35:53,180 --> 00:35:55,070
The music we usually create

848
00:35:55,220 --> 00:35:58,290
has a similar style,

849
00:35:58,300 --> 00:36:00,010
(They are similar.)

850
00:36:00,010 --> 00:36:02,380
so I feel we reach mutual
understanding very quickly.

851
00:36:02,580 --> 00:36:05,170
There is rarely any conflict.

852
00:36:05,300 --> 00:36:05,760
Yes.

853
00:36:05,760 --> 00:36:06,470
Then,

854
00:36:06,470 --> 00:36:11,460
regardless of whether it is working
together on a performance

855
00:36:11,460 --> 00:36:12,700
or preparing for it.

856
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:15,120
Even in our daily lives, we
would spend time together,

857
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:16,120
or having fun together,

858
00:36:16,300 --> 00:36:17,780
it all goes very smoothly.

859
00:36:18,590 --> 00:36:20,580
(Same thoughts)

860
00:36:20,580 --> 00:36:23,420
(Final's coming up. Who's your No.1?)
(Any words for yourself or the others?)

861
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,400
It's been two months.

862
00:36:27,210 --> 00:36:28,980
Honestly, I don't remember much.

863
00:36:28,980 --> 00:36:30,810
I just remember the feeling

864
00:36:30,810 --> 00:36:32,260
and how my mindset changed.

865
00:36:32,260 --> 00:36:33,770
(Mindset changes)
When I first got here,

866
00:36:33,770 --> 00:36:36,060
I was really nervous,
scared, and unsure.

867
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:38,170
But after getting closer to everyone,

868
00:36:38,540 --> 00:36:39,880
I started to feel more at ease.

869
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:40,370
Yeah.

870
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:44,460
I think my biggest growth
in these two months

871
00:36:45,140 --> 00:36:46,780
is gaining recognition.

872
00:36:46,780 --> 00:36:50,080
(Gained recognition and support)
That's something I never had before.

873
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:54,540
U.Jay, your dancing has improved a lot.

874
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:57,250
U.Jay.

875
00:36:57,900 --> 00:37:00,890
He can speak Thai now.

876
00:37:01,270 --> 00:37:03,070
(Best Breakthrough Award)
Yeah, you can speak Thai.

877
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,540
Great performance.

878
00:37:06,540 --> 00:37:07,740
It's very energetic.

879
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:11,990
And I can clearly see my own growth now.

880
00:37:12,170 --> 00:37:15,280
But what I've gained the most
is probably friendship.

881
00:37:15,280 --> 00:37:15,990
(Friendship)

882
00:37:15,990 --> 00:37:18,290
Everyone here,
both contestants and staff,

883
00:37:18,290 --> 00:37:20,310
comes from different parts of the world.

884
00:37:20,610 --> 00:37:23,280
Being able to meet
and get to know each other like this

885
00:37:23,280 --> 00:37:25,780
really means a lot.

886
00:37:26,530 --> 00:37:27,690
Maybe ten years from now,

887
00:37:27,690 --> 00:37:30,170
I'll still remember these moments
we shared.

888
00:37:30,170 --> 00:37:32,860
This has been an amazing journey

889
00:37:32,860 --> 00:37:33,650
for me.

890
00:37:35,410 --> 00:37:37,820
So who's your No.1?

891
00:37:38,170 --> 00:37:38,810
U.Jay.

892
00:37:38,810 --> 00:37:39,630
(Without hesitation)

893
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,900
Aside from Baekhyun,

894
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:47,520
he's the closest thing to a perfect idol
I've seen in real life.

895
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:49,500
(Happy and surprised)
That's too much praise.

896
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:52,480
For me, I'd say myself.

897
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:55,820
My fans really came through
and got me to first place.

898
00:37:56,340 --> 00:37:59,120
So I hope my future performances

899
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,990
can live up to that.

900
00:38:01,650 --> 00:38:03,350
As for me, I think

901
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:06,580
everyone here is my No.1.

902
00:38:06,580 --> 00:38:07,780
(Everyone is No.1)

903
00:38:07,780 --> 00:38:09,900
(Final's coming up. Who's your No.1?)
(Any words for yourself or the others?)

904
00:38:09,900 --> 00:38:11,680
I'd say U.Jay and Leo.

905
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:14,640
Yeah, they're both really strong,

906
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:17,380
and their scores are high too.

907
00:38:17,510 --> 00:38:18,210
Yeah.

908
00:38:18,210 --> 00:38:19,280
Personally,

909
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:21,640
if it's Chinese team, I'd pick U.Jay.

910
00:38:21,780 --> 00:38:24,060
If it's Thai team, I'd pick Cannon.

911
00:38:25,090 --> 00:38:25,720
Cannon.

912
00:38:27,900 --> 00:38:29,870
What I want to say is,

913
00:38:29,870 --> 00:38:33,240
you all know how talented you are.

914
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:36,340
You know your own charm

915
00:38:36,340 --> 00:38:37,130
and what makes you stand out.

916
00:38:37,130 --> 00:38:40,390
So let's keep going together.

917
00:38:40,390 --> 00:38:44,720
I hope everyone can stay on the path
they've chosen

918
00:38:44,950 --> 00:38:47,260
and find success.

919
00:38:47,260 --> 00:38:50,270
No matter what you end up doing,
I hope you succeed.

920
00:38:50,580 --> 00:38:55,770
After the show ends, I hope
we'll have the chance to meet again.

921
00:38:56,610 --> 00:38:58,680
I want to tell myself to be stronger

922
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:02,430
and stay committed to my goals.

923
00:39:02,860 --> 00:39:07,410
I don't want to be the kind of idol

924
00:39:07,410 --> 00:39:09,780
people scream for

925
00:39:09,780 --> 00:39:11,380
just because I look good.

926
00:39:11,830 --> 00:39:13,670
I want people to like me

927
00:39:13,670 --> 00:39:15,680
for my work

928
00:39:15,850 --> 00:39:17,640
and get drawn into it.

929
00:39:17,640 --> 00:39:22,650
I want to be seen as an artist.

930
00:39:24,910 --> 00:39:31,090
Honestly, I've known for a while

931
00:39:31,980 --> 00:39:33,140
that I probably won't win.

932
00:39:35,300 --> 00:39:37,640
My ranking isn't high.

933
00:39:41,650 --> 00:39:47,820
Sometimes I feel like
this place isn't for me.

934
00:39:49,250 --> 00:39:54,220
But that doesn't mean I've given up.

935
00:39:54,220 --> 00:39:54,980
I haven't.

936
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:58,590
I'll still keep doing my best.

937
00:39:59,500 --> 00:40:03,600
Every performance,
I give it everything I've got.

938
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:05,090
And I'll keep pushing myself.

939
00:40:06,940 --> 00:40:10,360
But more than anything,
I just wish everyone the best.

940
00:40:10,360 --> 00:40:11,950
I'll always be rooting for you guys.

941
00:40:12,430 --> 00:40:15,330
No matter

942
00:40:15,330 --> 00:40:18,820
what path you choose in the future,

943
00:40:21,050 --> 00:40:23,690
I'll keep supporting you.

944
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:26,700
It's the same for all my friends here.

945
00:40:27,020 --> 00:40:30,250
After the show ends,

946
00:40:30,250 --> 00:40:31,860
I hope we can stay close,

947
00:40:31,860 --> 00:40:34,390
and we can keep chatting

948
00:40:34,390 --> 00:40:36,080
and hanging out like before.

949
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:36,920
I'd really like that.

950
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:39,150
See you next time.

951
00:40:39,650 --> 00:40:41,020
Good luck, everyone.

952
00:40:42,570 --> 00:40:43,740
I'll always be here.

953
00:40:48,010 --> 00:40:49,470
If it were me,

954
00:40:49,470 --> 00:40:52,060
(Choosing U.Jay)
I'd pick U.Jay.

955
00:40:52,060 --> 00:40:55,000
(Choosing U.Jay +1)
Same as Deaw.

956
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:59,000
He has everything it takes
to be an artist.

957
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:01,950
On and off stage,

958
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:04,290
he works incredibly hard.

959
00:41:04,290 --> 00:41:06,780
Sometimes he even skips meals.

960
00:41:06,930 --> 00:41:09,840
Yeah, he forgets to eat

961
00:41:09,840 --> 00:41:11,160
and doesn't take care of himself.

962
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:14,110
I think he's the best choice for No.1.

963
00:41:14,650 --> 00:41:15,840
For me,

964
00:41:16,970 --> 00:41:18,500
(Choosing himself)
I'd choose myself.

965
00:41:18,500 --> 00:41:20,450
This whole journey here,

966
00:41:20,450 --> 00:41:21,720
meeting everyone

967
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:23,220
and everything I've experienced,

968
00:41:23,400 --> 00:41:27,390
has been part of my success.

969
00:41:27,390 --> 00:41:31,440
I also believe it's what

970
00:41:31,440 --> 00:41:38,110
defines success and victory for me.

971
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:45,780
(The show is ending.
Anything you want to say?)

972
00:41:45,780 --> 00:41:46,650
Alright, you go first.

973
00:41:48,370 --> 00:41:49,820
It's always me first.

974
00:41:50,570 --> 00:41:50,870
Okay.

975
00:41:50,870 --> 00:41:51,940
Go ahead, bro.

976
00:41:51,940 --> 00:41:52,680
Okay.

977
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:54,340
My thoughts?

978
00:41:54,740 --> 00:41:58,530
At the beginning, everyone saw it.

979
00:41:58,530 --> 00:42:01,420
It was hard for me.

980
00:42:01,720 --> 00:42:03,920
I had never danced before.

981
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:06,940
But I met this group of friends,

982
00:42:07,410 --> 00:42:10,070
from China, from Thailand, and him.

983
00:42:10,240 --> 00:42:13,240
Everyone kept encouraging me.

984
00:42:13,240 --> 00:42:16,660
After going through things together,

985
00:42:16,660 --> 00:42:18,830
we really built a bond.

986
00:42:18,830 --> 00:42:21,760
I've really enjoyed
being here with everyone.

987
00:42:21,760 --> 00:42:22,440
Yeah.

988
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:23,920
What about me?

989
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:26,010
I already mentioned you.

990
00:42:27,530 --> 00:42:30,580
- I...
- It's okay.

991
00:42:30,580 --> 00:42:31,240
Let me say it.

992
00:42:31,240 --> 00:42:33,130
When it comes to him,

993
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:35,990
I feel more comfortable speaking up

994
00:42:36,500 --> 00:42:39,000
and sharing what I think.

995
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:40,180
It's mainly thanks to him.

996
00:42:40,570 --> 00:42:44,020
Yeah, he helped me be more like myself.

997
00:42:44,220 --> 00:42:50,320
Even during practice,
when we were training for dance,

998
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:55,920
he really taught me.
He's like my dance teacher.

999
00:42:55,920 --> 00:42:56,560
Yeah.

1000
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,600
I understand what you were  saying.

1001
00:42:59,060 --> 00:42:59,840
Alright, my turn.

1002
00:42:59,840 --> 00:43:00,840
Firstly,

1003
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:04,420
people always say
happy times go by fast,

1004
00:43:04,660 --> 00:43:08,770
so honestly, it doesn't even feel real

1005
00:43:08,770 --> 00:43:09,990
that so much time has passed.

1006
00:43:09,990 --> 00:43:13,640
And I'm the youngest,

1007
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:15,830
all the older friends here
really took care of me.

1008
00:43:15,830 --> 00:43:17,860
Whenever there was good food,

1009
00:43:17,860 --> 00:43:20,460
they'd call me over to try it.

1010
00:43:20,460 --> 00:43:22,860
If I seemed upset,

1011
00:43:22,860 --> 00:43:24,540
they'd come comfort me.

1012
00:43:24,540 --> 00:43:28,690
So I feel like I've been
really well taken care of.

1013
00:43:30,630 --> 00:43:31,910
And also,

1014
00:43:35,090 --> 00:43:36,400
Ryu.

1015
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:41,950
It's actually hard

1016
00:43:42,200 --> 00:43:46,350
to find a friend
you click with this well,

1017
00:43:46,600 --> 00:43:51,000
someone you're this happy to be around.

1018
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:53,220
I'm really grateful

1019
00:43:53,220 --> 00:43:55,220
I met him here.

1020
00:43:55,580 --> 00:43:56,800
Honestly,

1021
00:43:57,560 --> 00:44:00,840
he's a very charming person.

1022
00:44:01,530 --> 00:44:03,900
I hope he can be more confident.

1023
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:06,020
And when people say

1024
00:44:06,020 --> 00:44:07,970
you're cute
or like a hamster,

1025
00:44:07,970 --> 00:44:10,490
that's not a bad thing.

1026
00:44:10,490 --> 00:44:12,460
That's your strength,

1027
00:44:12,460 --> 00:44:15,160
something others wish they had.

1028
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:16,830
It's what makes you unique.

1029
00:44:16,830 --> 00:44:18,480
You don't need to hide it.

1030
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:23,100
How should I put it...

1031
00:44:23,970 --> 00:44:25,290
And,

1032
00:44:25,470 --> 00:44:30,140
I really treasure every moment

1033
00:44:30,140 --> 00:44:32,280
we've spent hanging out.

1034
00:44:32,280 --> 00:44:35,170
Just enjoying the present

1035
00:44:35,170 --> 00:44:37,010
and having fun is enough.

1036
00:44:37,010 --> 00:44:38,740
As for the future,

1037
00:44:39,660 --> 00:44:41,340
I don't know what will happen.

1038
00:44:41,340 --> 00:44:44,300
Maybe I'll go back to my country,
and you'll be in Thailand.

1039
00:44:44,300 --> 00:44:45,480
We might not get to see each other much.

1040
00:44:45,480 --> 00:44:48,860
But I hope we can stay in touch.

1041
00:44:48,860 --> 00:44:51,770
And even if we don't talk often,

1042
00:44:51,770 --> 00:44:52,770
that's okay too.

1043
00:44:52,770 --> 00:44:55,450
Just remember

1044
00:44:55,450 --> 00:44:56,710
that right now,

1045
00:45:00,020 --> 00:45:01,190
we're having a great time together.

1046
00:45:01,660 --> 00:45:02,640
Wow.

1047
00:45:03,310 --> 00:45:04,400
Wow.

1048
00:45:05,070 --> 00:45:05,950
Wow.

1049
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:13,470
Three, two, one.

1050
00:45:13,470 --> 00:45:15,890
"Way To You" Up Up Up!

1051
00:45:16,030 --> 00:45:21,880
"Way To You" Up Up Up!

1052
00:45:21,960 --> 00:45:25,180
"Way To You" Up Up Up!

1053
00:45:25,890 --> 00:45:27,470
Goodbye!

1054
00:45:45,120 --> 00:45:49,140
After weeks of reality training
and live performance tests,

1055
00:45:49,140 --> 00:45:52,460
the contestants
have made it to the final night.

1056
00:45:53,890 --> 00:45:55,140
(The finals are about to begin)

1057
00:45:55,140 --> 00:45:56,650
(Ten contestants
from China and Thailand)

1058
00:45:56,650 --> 00:45:58,230
(A fierce battle for the top)

1059
00:45:58,230 --> 00:46:00,220
(A powerful comeback)

1060
00:46:03,710 --> 00:46:05,390
I'll never stop,

1061
00:46:05,460 --> 00:46:07,440
because you're behind me.

1062
00:46:08,410 --> 00:46:10,700
I came here to grow.

1063
00:46:11,980 --> 00:46:14,480
Hi everyone, I'm Eugene.

1064
00:46:15,450 --> 00:46:17,600
I'll do whatever it takes to succeed.

1065
00:46:18,920 --> 00:46:21,340
In my life, even a mess
can still be a perfect score.

1066
00:46:22,780 --> 00:46:24,420
I'll give it everything I've got.

1067
00:46:25,590 --> 00:46:27,560
I'm here on the final stage.
See you there.

1068
00:46:28,780 --> 00:46:31,050
I hope everyone can feel happy with me.

1069
00:46:32,220 --> 00:46:34,510
I came here to fight and give it my all.

1070
00:46:35,500 --> 00:46:37,430
There's no such thing
as giving up in my dictionary.

1071
00:46:40,460 --> 00:46:44,760
Contestants earned online votes

1072
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:47,730
through solo, duet, group,
and team performances.

1073
00:46:47,730 --> 00:46:51,680
Votes from all channels were counted,

1074
00:46:51,680 --> 00:46:54,480
closing on April 3rd at 10 PM.

1075
00:46:54,480 --> 00:46:55,870
The best pair will be decided.

1076
00:46:56,760 --> 00:47:00,210
(The competition is about to begin)

1077
00:47:11,670 --> 00:47:14,210
Please welcome all contestants
with the opening performance,

1078
00:47:14,210 --> 00:47:15,770
"Way To You".

1079
00:50:10,700 --> 00:50:13,290
Hello everyone.

1080
00:50:13,290 --> 00:50:16,050
Welcome to "Way To You".

1081
00:50:16,300 --> 00:50:18,780
Welcome!

1082
00:50:18,780 --> 00:50:20,110
Tonight,

1083
00:50:20,110 --> 00:50:24,380
we witness an important moment
for these ten contestants.

1084
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:27,250
Welcome to our 300 audience members
joining us today

1085
00:50:27,250 --> 00:50:31,690
to witness their big moment.

1086
00:50:31,690 --> 00:50:33,450
This is our final day,

1087
00:50:33,450 --> 00:50:36,690
and we also have a special guest.

1088
00:50:36,690 --> 00:50:38,370
He's...

1089
00:50:38,370 --> 00:50:43,440
the lead producer of the show, Boom.

1090
00:50:46,370 --> 00:50:51,150
Boom has watched their journey

1091
00:50:51,150 --> 00:50:53,560
from their first team-up,

1092
00:50:53,560 --> 00:50:55,270
their first dance,

1093
00:50:55,270 --> 00:50:57,630
their first performance.

1094
00:50:57,630 --> 00:50:59,500
So Boom,

1095
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:01,160
after seeing them today,

1096
00:51:01,160 --> 00:51:04,170
what feels different compared
to your first meeting with them?

1097
00:51:04,170 --> 00:51:06,020
What has changed?

1098
00:51:06,420 --> 00:51:09,780
Hello everyone, I'm Boom.

1099
00:51:10,190 --> 00:51:11,480
Welcome.

1100
00:51:12,380 --> 00:51:14,590
Let's welcome Boom once again.

1101
00:51:16,380 --> 00:51:18,820
I'm really happy to be back.

1102
00:51:19,040 --> 00:51:23,720
I think everyone feels the same as I do.

1103
00:51:23,980 --> 00:51:27,040
You've all improved so much

1104
00:51:27,290 --> 00:51:30,800
in such a short time.

1105
00:51:31,440 --> 00:51:33,910
Every single one of you is impressive.

1106
00:51:34,590 --> 00:51:37,870
It's not just normal progress,

1107
00:51:37,870 --> 00:51:40,920
but it's a huge leap forward.

1108
00:51:40,920 --> 00:51:42,710
You all have great potential.

